Hi Tony.  

Last minute flights can be expensive. Most of the time you need a 7-day advanced purchase to get a discount. 

The best tool that Iâve found for comparing airfares and finding the cheapest fares is through the Google Flights website. (www.flights.google.com).   There are some purchase links through google flights, but I recommend that once you find flights that work for you through Google Flights that you actually book the flights directly with the airline you choose - either through the airlineâs website or through their app.  If you run into any problems with your flights for any reason, if you have purchased your ticket through a 3rd party rather than from the airline directly, the airline may not be willing to help you. 

The other thing I recommend is looking at alternate airports.  You have 3 airports to choose from up there (San Jose, Oakland, San Francisco) and you might find that one airport is cheaper than the other for this weekend.  And down here, you can look at either Burbank or LAX.  Playing with different combinations of airports can often lead to cheaper fares.  

One word of caution about using Google Flights (and any online site) is that Southwest Airlines does not usually show up in their searches.  That is because Southwest generally wonât pay to show up in their listings.  So if you want to consider Southwest, you have to go directly to their website at www.southwest.com or their app to check prices.
